fastest measured on the surface of the planet 
at 121 pm tuesday the wind was a mere 2 mph which is 
highly unusual gordon said 
the 6288foot mountain has some of the worlds harshest 
weather its hurricaneforce winds above 74 mph are registered an 
average 100 days a year the average annual snowfall is 178 inches 
the coldest it has ever been on the mountain is minus 47 
degrees the warmest 71 degrees snow falls on the mountain in 
every month and the peak is socked in by clouds 30 days a year 
