<TEXT>
charges of deception are flying between safety 
advocates and audi importers following a consumer coalitions 
request that all 50 states prohibit advertisements claiming that 
the cars are unusually safe 
three consumer groups made the request in petitions sent tuesday 
to the attorney general in each of the states 
the center for auto safety of washington the audi victims 
network of plainview ny and the new york public interest 
research group said audi of america misled consumers in 
advertisements published in march and april declaring the audi 5000 
is among the safest cars in the us 
we ask that you put an end to this deceptive advertising by 
audi said the petitions 
the organizations said at least one out of every 145 audi 5000s 
sold in the united states has experienced sudden acceleration 
problems in which the car accelerates for no apparent reason 
audis us parent company volkswagen of america inc in turn 
accused the safety advocates of distorting numbers to mislead the 
public 
it is bloody near criminal the way theyre playing with 
numbers said joseph bennett volkswagen spokesman in troy mich 
thats a baldfaced lie and they know it 
audi last year recalled 255336 of its 197886 audi 5000s for 
installation of a shiftlock device to fix reported throttle 
problems on the cars the devices keeps a driver from putting the 
car in gear unless the brake is depressed 
the consumers groups allege driver complaints show the device 
doesnt prevent unintended acceleration 
they said each incident of unintended acceleration carries 
with it the potential for loss of life and serious injuries 
indeed already at least five people have died and over 2000 have 
had the daylights scared out of them as a result of audis running 
amuck 
bennett argued that a complaint of sudden acceleration does not 
necessarily mean such a problem actually occurred 
the company in documents filed this week with national highway 
traffic safety administration analyzed 394 reports of unintended 
acceleration involving cars equipped with the shiftlock device it 
said it found that all but 22 of the reports were flawed 
