university said in a telephone interview late tuesday it 
bothers me very much that the president would allow somebody to 
come through and put words in his mouth 
reedy said the misattributed shultz remarks which followed the 
shooting down of a korean air lines passenger plane in 1983 and 
the madeup quotations attributed to reagan at the geneva summit 
in 1985 are fairly harmless but thats not the point 
suppose those words got the united states embroiled in some 
real crisis of some sort he said its one thing if the 
president makes a mistake and gets the nation in a crisis but to 
have a statement drawn up by a technician with the presidents name 
stamped on it to get us into a crisis is too much 
