india has been given approval to buy 12 
million metric tons of us wheat at subsidized prices the 
agriculture department said wednesday 
acting undersecretary richard w goldberg said india will be 
allowed to buy the grain under the departments export enhancement 
program or eep it is the first time india has been eligible to 
buy subsidized wheat under the program although vegetable oil has 
been made available 
a metric ton is about 2205 pounds and is equal to 367 bushels 
of wheat 
under eep arrangements exporters can sell specified us 
commodities to designated countries at reduced prices in order to 
meet foreign competition and then collect free government surpluses 
of grain or other commodities as bonuses or subsidies 
subsidies have ranged from less than 20 to more than 40 per 
ton of wheat or in the range of 54 cents to 109 per bushel 
the soviet union also has been a big buyer of us wheat under 
eep with purchases totaling more than 118 million tons in the 
last year and china has bought more than 5 million tons under the 
program 
