<TEXT>
behind the stern granite face of the allegheny 
county courthouse and jail kate soffel whispered her 
turnofthecentury scheme of passion and escape with the 
imprisoned biddle boys 
more than eight decades later and four years after the movie 
mrs soffel her courthouse on sunday marks 100 years since 
completion the last major work by henry hobson richardson who 
helped shape american architecture 
you know a richardson building when you see it either that or 
a copy of one said george white current architect of the us 
capitol 
richardson was said to be aiming for a dignified pile of 
rocks the result was the fortresslike blocklong courthouse 
and jail joined by a great stone walkway over ross street that is 
still known by grimfaced prisoners and passersby as the bridge 
of sighs 
other famous richardson works include trinity church in boston 
marshall field wholesale store in chicago city hall in albany 
ny and town hall in north easton mass 
many late 19th century buildings imitate richardsons revival of 
the medievel european roman style that came to be known as 
richardsonian romanesque 
architect frank lloyd wright was said to be enchanted by the 
courthouse calling it worth all the other buildings in 
pittsburgh put together 
it might have been pittsburghers of the 1880s were horrified by 
richardsons extravagant plans and the 23 million pricetag 
expensive 8footlong granite slabs used to build the arches 
were displayed on street corners by critics according to james w 
knox a county planning director who has worked in the courthouse 
for 42 years 
they said the halls were too big the courtroom ceilings were 
too high knox said 
but pittsburgh led the nation in iron work and steelmaking and 
officials wanted a grand courthouse to serve the growing city 
and yet after being selected from about 100 american 
architects richardson died a year before the building was 
completed let me but have time to finish pittsburgh and i should 
