ark and natchez miss 
international paper and its unions have been at odds for more 
than a year over contracts that have come up for renewal at the 
heart of the disagreement is the issue of whether local contracts 
should restore premium pay for sundays and holidays 
premium pay had been eliminated with labors approval from past 
contracts but an improved financial picture for the industry in 
the last year prompted the unions to campaign to revive the benefit 
international paper has continued to operate its mills with 
replacement workers the company has claimed throughout the dispute 
